        <briefdescription>
<para>\par \b Module Contract\/ \:</para>
<para>\par \b Purpose\/ \:  To define TabbyPdfError — raised when the TabbyPDF external processing tool returns an error. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>\par \b Scope\/ \:  TabbyPDF processing error signalling. \par \b Input\/ \:  Error context (msg, filename, version). \par \b Output\/ \:  TabbyPdfError with HTTP 500 Internal Server Error code. \par \b Links\/ \:  [USES_API(9): <ref refid="classdedoc_1_1common_1_1exceptions_1_1dedoc__error_1_1DedocError" kindref="compound">dedoc.common.exceptions.dedoc_error.DedocError</ref>] \par \b Invariants\/ \:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>ALWAYS carries HTTP code 500 (external tool failure is a server-side dependency error).</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Inherits full DedocError API (msg_api, filename, version, metadata). \par \b Rationale\/ \:</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>Q: Why code=500? A: TabbyPDF is a server-side dependency — its failures are infrastructure errors, not client mistakes. \par \b Changes\/ \:</para>
<para>LAST_CHANGE: [v1.0.0 — Semantic template markup and LDD logging added.] \par \b Module Map\/ \:</para>
<para>CLASS 8[Exception for TabbyPDF external tool errors, always HTTP 500] =&gt; TabbyPdfError \par \b Use Cases\/ \:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>[TabbyPdfError]: PDFProcessor → CallTabbyPDF → TabbyPDFFails → RaiseTabbyPdfError → APIResponds500 </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
